Jeep Liberty Air Bags Under U.S. Probe for Unneeded Deployment

-- B y   A n g e l a   G r e i l i n g   K e a n e
-- 
2011-09-27T10:38:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-27/jeep-liberty-air-bags-under-u-s-probe-for-unneeded-deployment.html
Chrysler Group LLC’s Jeep Liberty
sport-utility vehicles are under investigation in the U.S. after
reports of front air bags suddenly deploying without a crash.   Model years 2002 and 2003 of the SUVs are the subject of a
U.S. National Highway Traffic Safety Administration
investigation, announced today on the regulator’s website,
following seven consumer complaints.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Angela Greiling Keane in Washington at 
 agreilingkea@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
JoAnne Norton at 
 jnorton@bloomberg.net  